This paper deals with the performance of neural network models on geometric transformations and adversarial perturbations, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-off between invariance and robustness, which is relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses training augmentation and adversarial training techniques, which are common in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
